enough for us to assume a position on the EU's recommendation 
concerning the temporary division of Danube waters. Gyorgy 
Tatar claims, moreover, that the Slovak attitude actually 
confirms our negative stand on the EU recommendation, which, 
according to Hungarian newspapers, proposes that 40 percent of 
the Danube water remain in the river's original bed and that 
Budapest build two small dams on its territory. 
